{
  "stem": "33.2",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "The only way we could sleep was on our side.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "If one person had to turn, of course everybody else had to.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "We-- our-- the person responsible for each barracks, the so-called block elder, 'blockalteste,' was usually a woman from Poland or Slovakia.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "These people have been in Auschwitz for years.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "Actually, they built the camp.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Very few of them survived at that point, not because of gas chambers, but because of winters and hard labor and lack of everything.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 48,
      "text": "Those who survived, it was the survival of the fittest, basically.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 49,
      "text": "Those who survived were really hardened human beings.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 50,
      "text": "They could not forgive us that we had a normal life while they were already suffering.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 51,
      "text": "And we really felt that hatred very intensively.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 52,
      "text": "They tried to tell us from the beginning that we'll never see our mothers or the children or anybody who we were separated from.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 53,
      "text": "They pointed at the other side, and they said-- they showed that in Camp H for Heaven, 'himmel' in German.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 54,
      "text": "First we didn't want to believe them, because we thought they're just mean and they just really hate us.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 55,
      "text": "But, as time went by, nobody ever came back, so we started to believe that what they're telling us is the truth.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 56,
      "text": "We had roll calls every morning as early as 3, 4 o'clock, and again later at night.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 57,
      "text": "The roll calls were really not to count people, because escaping was impossible, the high voltage electricity in those barbed wires that surrounded us.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 58,
      "text": "The roll calls were used for two purposes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 59,
      "text": "Our miserable food was given to us during roll calls, which consisted of some soup with some rotten vegetables floating in it.",
      "word_count": 22
    }
  ],
